Title : Thomas Whitefield
Text : {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}
{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}
'''Thomas Whitefield''' ([[floruit|fl.]] 1378–1401) was an English politician.

He was [[Mayor of Hereford]] in the period November 1383 – October 1384 and in 1393–1395. He was elected a [[Member of Parliament|Member]] (MP) of the [[Parliament of England]] for [[Hereford (UK Parliament constituency)|Hereford]] in 1378 and 1401.<ref>http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/whitefield-thomas</ref>

